instructions:
## Set Up Liveblocks Real-Time Collaboration in Next.js

### 1. Create a Liveblocks account
- Go to liveblocks.io and create a free account.
- Create a new project and note your **Public Key** (`pk_...`) and **Secret Key** (`sk_...`).
- Add to `.env.local`:
  ```
  NEXT_PUBLIC_LIVEBLOCKS_PUBLIC_KEY=pk_your_public_key
  LIVEBLOCKS_SECRET_KEY=sk_your_secret_key
  ```
- The Public Key is safe to expose to the browser. The Secret Key must NEVER be in client-side code.

### 2. Install packages
- Run: `npm install @liveblocks/client @liveblocks/react`
- For Liveblocks + Tiptap collaborative editor: `npm install @liveblocks/react-tiptap @tiptap/react @tiptap/pm @tiptap/starter-kit yjs y-prosemirror`
- For Liveblocks + Lexical: `npm install @liveblocks/react-lexical`
- If using pnpm or yarn, use the equivalent commands.

### 3. Configure the Liveblocks client
- Create `src/liveblocks.config.ts`:
  ```ts
  import { createClient } from '@liveblocks/client';
  import { createRoomContext } from '@liveblocks/react';

  // Define your presence shape — what each user broadcasts to others
  type Presence = {
    cursor: { x: number; y: number } | null;
    name: string;
  };

  // Define your storage shape — shared persistent state
  type Storage = {
    // e.g. notes: LiveList<LiveObject<{ id: string; text: string }>>;
  };

  // Define user metadata (returned from your auth endpoint)
  type UserMeta = {
    id: string;
    info: {
      name: string;
      color: string;
      avatar?: string;
    };
  };

  const client = createClient({
    publicApiKey: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_LIVEBLOCKS_PUBLIC_KEY!,
    // For authenticated rooms, replace publicApiKey with:
    // authEndpoint: '/api/liveblocks-auth',
  });

  export const {
    RoomProvider,
    useRoom,
    useMyPresence,
    useUpdateMyPresence,
    useOthers,
    useOthersMapped,
    useStorage,
    useMutation,
    useSelf,
  } = createRoomContext<Presence, Storage, UserMeta>(client);
  ```
- Keep all Liveblocks hooks imported from this single config file — never import directly from `@liveblocks/react`.

### 4. Wrap your page with RoomProvider
- Create a `Room` client component wrapper:
  ```tsx
  // src/components/room.tsx
  'use client';
  import { RoomProvider } from '@/liveblocks.config';
  import { ReactNode } from 'react';

  export function Room({ id, children }: { id: string; children: ReactNode }) {
    return (
      <RoomProvider
        id={id}
        initialPresence={{ cursor: null, name: 'Anonymous' }}
      >
        {children}
      </RoomProvider>
    );
  }
  ```
- In your Server Component page:
  ```tsx
  // app/docs/[id]/page.tsx
  import { Room } from '@/components/room';
  import { DocumentEditor } from '@/components/document-editor';

  export default function Page({ params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
    return (
      <Room id={`doc-${params.id}`}>
        <DocumentEditor />
      </Room>
    );
  }
  ```
- Room IDs can be any string. Use a meaningful prefix like `doc-`, `board-` to namespace rooms.

### 5. Live cursors (presence)
- In a Client Component inside the Room:
  ```tsx
  'use client';
  import { useMyPresence, useOthersMapped } from '@/liveblocks.config';

  export function LiveCursors() {
    const [, updateMyPresence] = useMyPresence();
    const others = useOthersMapped((other) => other.presence.cursor);

    return (
      <div
        className="relative w-full h-full"
        onPointerMove={(e) => {
          const rect = e.currentTarget.getBoundingClientRect();
          updateMyPresence({
            cursor: { x: e.clientX - rect.left, y: e.clientY - rect.top },
          });
        }}
        onPointerLeave={() => updateMyPresence({ cursor: null })}
      >
        {others.map(([id, cursor]) =>
          cursor ? (
            <div
              key={id}
              className="absolute pointer-events-none"
              style={{ left: cursor.x, top: cursor.y }}
            >
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
                <path d="M0 0L0 16L4 12L7 16L9 15L6 11L11 11Z" fill="#0ea5e9" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          ) : null
        )}
      </div>
    );
  }
  ```
- `useMyPresence` returns `[myPresence, updateMyPresence]`. Only call `updateMyPresence` with the fields you want to change — it merges, not replaces.

### 6. Shared storage (persistent state)
- Storage is persisted by Liveblocks across sessions (unlike presence which is ephemeral).
- Define storage types in `liveblocks.config.ts`:
  ```ts
  import { LiveList, LiveObject } from '@liveblocks/client';
  type Storage = {
    notes: LiveList<LiveObject<{ id: string; text: string; color: string }>>;
  };
  ```
- Read storage:
  ```tsx
  const notes = useStorage((root) => root.notes);
  ```
- Mutate storage:
  ```tsx
  const addNote = useMutation(({ storage }) => {
    storage.get('notes').push(
      new LiveObject({ id: crypto.randomUUID(), text: '', color: '#fff' })
    );
  }, []);
  ```
- Always initialize storage in `RoomProvider`:
  ```tsx
  <RoomProvider
    id={roomId}
    initialPresence={{ cursor: null, name: 'Anonymous' }}
    initialStorage={{
      notes: new LiveList([]),
    }}
  >
  ```

### 7. Collaborative text editing with Tiptap
- Create a collaborative editor component:
  ```tsx
  'use client';
  import { useEditor, EditorContent } from '@tiptap/react';
  import StarterKit from '@tiptap/starter-kit';
  import Collaboration from '@tiptap/extension-collaboration';
  import CollaborationCursor from '@tiptap/extension-collaboration-cursor';
  import { useRoom, useSelf } from '@/liveblocks.config';
  import * as Y from 'yjs';
  import { LiveblocksYjsProvider } from '@liveblocks/yjs';
  import { useMemo } from 'react';

  export function CollaborativeEditor() {
    const room = useRoom();
    const self = useSelf();
    const { doc, provider } = useMemo(() => {
      const doc = new Y.Doc();
      const provider = new LiveblocksYjsProvider(room, doc);
      return { doc, provider };
    }, [room]);

    const editor = useEditor({
      extensions: [
        StarterKit.configure({ history: false }),
        Collaboration.configure({ document: doc }),
        CollaborationCursor.configure({
          provider,
          user: { name: self?.info.name ?? 'Anonymous', color: self?.info.color ?? '#0ea5e9' },
        }),
      ],
    });

    return <EditorContent editor={editor} />;
  }
  ```
- Install the additional packages: `npm install @liveblocks/yjs @tiptap/extension-collaboration @tiptap/extension-collaboration-cursor`
- `history: false` is REQUIRED — Collaboration extension provides its own undo/redo via Yjs.

### 8. Auth endpoint (for private rooms)
- For production, replace `publicApiKey` with an auth endpoint:
  ```ts
  // liveblocks.config.ts
  const client = createClient({ authEndpoint: '/api/liveblocks-auth' });
  ```
- Create `src/app/api/liveblocks-auth/route.ts`:
  ```ts
  import { Liveblocks } from '@liveblocks/node';
  import { NextRequest } from 'next/server';

  const liveblocks = new Liveblocks({ secret: process.env.LIVEBLOCKS_SECRET_KEY! });

  export async function POST(request: NextRequest) {
    // Authenticate your user here (e.g., from session/JWT)
    const user = await getServerSession(); // use your auth system
    if (!user) return new Response('Unauthorized', { status: 401 });

    const { status, body } = await liveblocks.identifyUser(
      { userId: user.id, groupIds: [] },
      {
        userInfo: {
          name: user.name ?? 'Anonymous',
          color: '#' + Math.floor(Math.random() * 0xffffff).toString(16).padStart(6, '0'),
          avatar: user.image ?? undefined,
        },
      }
    );
    return new Response(body, { status });
  }
  ```
- Install the server package: `npm install @liveblocks/node`

### 9. Verify the integration
- Start the dev server: `npm run dev`.
- Open the same page in two browser windows.
- Move the cursor in one window — verify it appears in the other.
- If using storage: add an item in one window — verify it appears in the other instantly.
- Check the Liveblocks dashboard (liveblocks.io) — you should see active rooms and connections.

### Common Errors
- **'RoomProvider must be used inside a Room'** — You are using a Liveblocks hook outside `<RoomProvider>`. Ensure your page wraps the client component tree with `<RoomProvider>`.
- **'publicApiKey is not defined'** — `NEXT_PUBLIC_LIVEBLOCKS_PUBLIC_KEY` is not set in `.env.local`, or you forgot the `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix (required for browser-accessible env vars).
- **'Cannot read properties of null (reading presence)'** — You are accessing `useOthers()` results without checking for null cursor. Always check `if (cursor)` before rendering cursor elements.
- **Presence updates cause full re-renders** — Use `useOthersMapped` instead of `useOthers` to select only the presence fields you need, avoiding unnecessary re-renders.
- **Collaborative editor shows duplicate content** — You have `history: true` (default) in StarterKit with the Collaboration extension. Set `StarterKit.configure({ history: false })`.
- **Auth endpoint returns 401 unexpectedly** — Verify `LIVEBLOCKS_SECRET_KEY` is set (not the public key). The secret key starts with `sk_`.
- **Storage mutations don't persist after reload** — You are mutating presence instead of storage. Presence is ephemeral. Use `useMutation` with `storage.get(...)` for persistent state.
- **'LiveblocksYjsProvider is not exported'** — Install `@liveblocks/yjs`: `npm install @liveblocks/yjs`.

### What NOT to do
- Do NOT import hooks directly from `@liveblocks/react` — always import from your `liveblocks.config.ts` to get proper TypeScript types.
- Do NOT put `publicApiKey` in server-side code or share `secretKey` with the browser — the secret key must only be in server-side API routes.
- Do NOT use `useOthers()` to render cursors without `useOthersMapped` — it subscribes to all presence changes and causes excessive re-renders.
- Do NOT use Liveblocks storage for large binary files or media — it is designed for structured JSON-like data. Store files in S3/R2 and reference URLs.
- Do NOT use presence for persistent data — presence is cleared when a user disconnects. Use storage for anything that must survive page refreshes.
- Do NOT set `history: true` (or leave it default) in StarterKit when using the Collaboration extension — this causes conflicts with Yjs undo/redo.
- Do NOT create a new Y.Doc inside the component render function without `useMemo` — it will recreate the document on every render, destroying collaborative state.
